cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the recent progress on neural approaches to conversational AI, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also addresses challenges in developing intelligent dialog systems, which involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the importance of consistency and interactiveness in dialog systems, which are related to user experience and human-computer interaction, respectively, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) possible categories. Finally, the paper presents a review of recent works on neural approaches, which involves model architectures and training techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
